/*!
\page mathfunctions_deg2rad DEG2RAD Convert From Degrees To Radians

<p>
Section: \ref sec_mathfunctions "Mathematical Functions"
\section Usage
Converts the argument from degrees to radians.  The
syntax for its use is
\verbatim
   y = deg2rad(x)
\endverbatim
where <tt>x</tt> is a numeric array.  Conversion is done by
simply multiplying <tt>x</tt> by <tt>pi/180</tt>.
\section Example
How many radians in a circle:

\if FRAGMENT
frag_mathfunctions_deg2rad_000.m
0
deg2rad(360) - 2*pi
\endif


